<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-631-713  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 631 713.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  Nov 12 1990 v20 n5p30(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Crosfield enhances Lightspeed kerning; Release 2.5 adds newfeatures. (The Latest Word) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Crosfield Lightspeed Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Lightspeed Color Layout System 2.5 (Desktop publishing software)(Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Desktop PublishingSoftware PackagesEnhancementsProduct IntroductionColorLayoutKerning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Crosfield enhances Lightspeed kerning Crosfield has introduced a new,interactive kerning featurefor its Lightspeed Color Layout System.andP;  Theutility enables the operator to modify Bitstream font metrics to achievebetter character spacing when using the system's kerning and trackingcapabilities.andM;After the metrics are changed, the new values apply to all files that arecomposed, including those that have been composed earlier using differentvalues.andP;  That is, the same files processed again will look better based onthe new values, but they may produce different results because the spacingwill differ.andM;Other enhancements to the system, part of release 2.5, include support forEncapsulated PostScript files that handle vignettes, type, drawings, etc.;andO;the ability to retain the names of images imported in TIFF from a Studiosystem via StudioLink, so that high-resolution images can be automaticallyrecalled by the Studio system during page assembly; improved tabularcomposition; and support for importing files in PINP text image format.andO;</TEXT></DOC>